&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Overview&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Understood is seeking a contractor to support &lt;strong&gt;program development&lt;/strong&gt; on a deliverables-driven, time-limited basis. This is a contract role—not a full-time employee position—and the contractor will be engaged for their specialized expertise to complete clearly defined outputs within the contract term.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Scope of Work / Key deliverables&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The contractor will be responsible for the following:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and support the launch of new programs from concept to rollout, pulling together existing tech and non-tech capabilities into coherent, well-defined offerings.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Audit current capabilities across teams, identify gaps and overlaps, and shape them into structured programs with clear goals, scope, and ownership.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish the operational foundation for each program, including workflows, documentation, tooling, and processes, that internal teams can run independently after handoff.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Engage with cross-functional stakeholders (product, engineering, operations, leadership) to align program design with company priorities and resourcing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define KPIs and reporting frameworks, establish baselines, and illustrate early impact to leadership.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide a clean handoff to internal owners, including documentation, training, and transition support.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Note: Contractors maintain control over the means and methods of completing their work, provided they meet all deliverables.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven track record designing and launching programs from scratch, ideally in a tech or tech-enabled environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong systems thinking, able to take scattered capabilities and organize them into something coherent and operable.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent stakeholder management, able to align senior leaders and working teams without formal authority.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bias toward action and self-direction; you can operate with ambiguity and minimal ramp-up.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience building lightweight, durable processes and documentation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with STEM education, workforce development, or neurodiversity&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with school- or educator-facing program models&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfort working across both technical and non-technical teams and translating between them.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Existing relationships with STEM funders, implementation partners, or evaluation organizations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Contract Details&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Estimated Hours&lt;/strong&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;~20 hours a week for approximately 6 months, with a defined scope of standing up to 2-3 programs and handing them off.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must be able to work EST hour&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Compensation:&lt;/strong&gt; $100/hour, rate commensurate with experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contractor is responsible for all taxes, insurance, and equipment required to perform services.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
